Pneumococcal causes middle ear infection, but also severe infections including meningitis and blood poisoning.
Pneumococcal infections kill up to 28 children up to 10 years old each year after examination in hospitals.
Outside the Czech Republic, the mandatory vaccination of children against pneumococcal disease was introduced in about 40 countries.
Will vaccination be mandatory?
At the same time, it is said that this vaccination could be mandatory in the future.
Starting in January, it will be paid by the insurance companies and will be voluntary.
That compulsory vaccination would be better, mentioned, for example, the head of the Nahlas Citizens' Association, Rudolf Kalovsky.
