According to Spanish legislation, a vehicle whose chassis number has been unregistered may no longer be driven on the roads, but certain parts that are not damaged may be used as spare parts.
The cars with historical value, on the other hand, may be re-registered, even if they have been unregistered after difficult procedures by the authorities.
Cost estimate of the workshop in four steps
With the Auda-Taller tool, Audatex ensures that the user receives a cost estimate in just four steps: identification of the vehicle, search for the spare part, preparation and creation of a cost estimate.
The ease of use of these systems is a fundamental condition, especially to convince the older professionals, who are usually more or less against the use of these new computer techniques.
The database includes 1,034 vehicles, 666 of which are passenger vehicles, 109 off-road vehicles, 137 motorcycles, 78 vans and 44 trucks.
Of course, you need a computer with an internet connection to use.
After the model to be repaired has been identified by means of the chassis number, a graphic of the respective model appears and the required spare part is then selected.
The user can include variables such as the price of the working hours, surcharges or discounts and afterwards he can have the cost estimate printed and passed on to his customer.
However, AudaTaller is not a tool for peer review like AudaPlus, but rather a reference catalog.
The main difference between the two systems is that the workshop-oriented does not include estimated working hours.
The cost of use for this tool is 350 euros per year, an amount that the customer can easily pay.
The company Audatex is currently working to be able to offer these images in three-dimensional format.
This is an innovation that car mechanics have been waiting for a long time, as it allows you to select a door, for example, and then turn the picture completely to look at the inside.
